snippet.textDisplay:
The offload 3:17 really nice and classiest pass thus far in this Series.



Chiefs looking good and if I am being 100% honest, the Blues are massively improved, but other than that, hmm, not as dominant. Still the All-Blacks could for sure build a very strong squad capable of dispatching the likes of South Africa and England, so all in all, may not be as dominant in the Super rugby, but future wise for the All-Blacks, I would say not looking to shabby.

snippet.textDisplay:
Waz going about it the right way; getting back into Super Rugby, showing he has the knack for winning with whatever team he has, thus placing himself in pole position when the AB's job comes up again in two years time*. Razor should look for an international post in the NH over the next few years (I get the feeling Scotland may be in the market kinda soon), he's still young for a coach and the experience would only make him better.


*The current line-up has a distinct caretaker look and feel to it, and the two-year initial contract doesn't indicate overwhelming confidence from higher up. One or two average-to-lousy showings in the Rugby Championship and the job will likely be up for grabs.
